brainly_data.question: A python curls up to touch the tip of its own tail with its nose, forming the shape of a circle. The python is 2.6 pie meters long what is the radius of r of the circle that the python forms
brainly_data.subject: Mathematics

all_answers.question: A python curls up to touch the tip of its own tail with its nose, forming the shape of a circle. The python is 2.6 pie meters long what is the radius of r of the circle that the python forms
all_answers.subject: Mathematics
all_answers.text: 1.3 meters because the radius is half of the diameter, which is 2.6
